===Etymology 1===
{{OE.}} ''[[pund]]'', from {{Ger.}} ''*punda-'', an early borrowing from {{L.}} ''[[pondo|pondō]]'' in ''[[libra|lībra]] [[pondo|pondō]]'' ‘a pound by weight’ (a misinterpretation: ''[[pondo|pondō]]'' is the adverb meaning ‘by weight’, originally an ablative form of ''[[pondus]]''). Cognate with Dutch ''[[pond]]'', German ''[[Pfund]]'', Swedish ''[[pund]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[unit]] of [[weight]]: of 16 [[ounce]]s in the [[avoirdupois]] system (= 453.592 g) or of 12 [[troy ounce]]s in the [[troy weight|troy system]] (= 373.242 g). Its symbol is [[lb]].
# [[pound-force|Pound-force]].
# {{US}} The symbol '''#''' <!--isn't this "pound sign" rather than "pound"?-->
# A unit of [[currency]] used in Cyprus; Egypt; Lebanon; the United Kingdom and its [[dependency|dependencies]]; and formerly in the Republic of Ireland (which now uses the [[euro]]). Its symbol is <big>[[£]]</big>.

